new.name: CVE-2025-8088-Exploit
new.description: A proof-of-concept exploit for WinRAR vulnerability (CVE-2025-8088) affecting versions 7.12 and lower. This tool creates a malicious RAR archive that embeds payloads in Alternate Data Streams (ADS) with path traversal, potentially leading to arbitrary code execution.
